1.  Servlet API
    - protocols TCP/IP, HTTP (Request, Response) -> Http Headers and Methods
    - maven dependencies servlets and jstl
    - webapp folder structure
    - web.xml - config web app file
    - config via XML and Annotation
    - Servlet API Hierarchy
        Servlet <- GenericServlet <- HttpServlet <- YourServlet

        Servlet lifecycle (init,service,destroy)

        Tomcat - servlet container. It knows how to create, call, and destroy servlets

    Memory places in tomcat - ServletContext->SessionContext->RequestContext->PageContext

    Filter and Listeners

    Java + html = Jsp (dynamic page)

    Scriplets->JSTL

    Cookies -> HttpSession

    Tomcat folder structure

    redirect and forward

    future: see SpringMVC

